<TEXT>
a mistrial was declared friday in the bank 
fraud trial of us rep harold ford after the jury said it was 
hopelessly deadlocked 
the congressman was accused of taking political favors in the 
form of loans that prosecutors said he was never expected to repay 
to tennessee banking brothers jake and ch butcher jr 
jury foreman ho robinson reported the deadlock after us 
district judge odell horton removed one of the 12 panel members for 
failing to disclose a past felony conviction that development did 
not figure in the mistrial 
ford a 44yearold memphis democrat had been on trial since 
feb 12 on charges of conspiracy bank and mail fraud a conviction 
could have brought a sentence of up to 95 years 
the congressman said he regarded the mistrial as a victory 
though he had hoped for acquittal 
im hopeful now that i can put this episode behind me ford 
said 
but us attorney john gill in knoxville said there would be 
another trial 
the only thing i can say is we had a case we felt we were 
obligated to bring based on the evidence we had gill said 
ford stood trial with former butcher accountant david crabtree 
and former butcher lawyers karl schledwitz and douglas beaty 
ford the states only black member of congress has complained 
often since his indictment that he is the victim of racist 
prosecutors an allegation the government has denied 
the government called 29 witnesses in the case the defense did 
not call any and ford said he decided not to testify because he 
regarded the governments case as weak 
on wednesday after their first two days of deliberations 
jurors returned to the courtroom to report they were deadlocked 
horton told them it was too early to give up work 
before the mistrial was declared friday assistant us attorney 
dan clancy asked horton to question juror juanita ruffin because 
the government believed she had a criminal record that she did not 
disclose during jury selection 
every juror picked for the trial signed a form on which they 
answered a variety of questions including whether they had ever 
been convicted of a crime 
horton confronted mrs ruffin in the courtroom about her record 
and she acknowledged she had been convicted in 1970 in connection 
with the theft of 160 she said she was placed on probation for 
that felony offense 
mrs ruffin also said she was convicted twice for shoplifting in 
the 1970s 
horton asked her why she didnt disclose the felony conviction 
during jury selection she said she thought she didnt have to 
because the offenses occurred more than 10 years earlier 
while being questioned mrs ruffin said the jury was split on 
reaching a verdict by a vote of 93 she did not say if that vote 
was in favor of acquittal or conviction 
the jury was down to 11 members when the mistrial was declared 
but lawyers said the judge could have allowed the deliberations to 
continue 
first elected to congress in 1974 ford has faced little 
opposition since then for his 9th congressional district seat 
he was charged with 19 criminal counts in an indictment handed 
down by a grand jury in knoxville in 1987 
his codefendants accused of helping him get and hde butcher 
money faced charges of conspiracy and mail fraud five counts for 
crabtree and 16 each for beaty and schledwitz 
ch butcher jr was brought to a nearby jail in wynne ark 
but was never asked to testify he and jake a twotime candidate 
for tennessee governor are serving 20year prison terms for bank 
fraud 
the 1983 collapse of their banking chain was one of the worst in 
us financial history 
the government said ford and his family drew butcher loans 
totaling more than 1 million between 1976 and 1982 but ford put 
the total at 650000 he said those debts were settled 
</TEXT>
