a 15yearold girl who said she was 
kidnapped chained to a tree and raped repeatedly for three weeks 
told police she escaped and killed her captor with his own shotgun 
while he slept 
her escape prompted a search friday for remains of two other 
missing girls after police found a crudely drawn map suggesting two 
girls had been killed and dismembered 
the map was discovered at the larue county campsite of phillip 
e clopton 39 of louisville who was found dead thursday after 
the louisville girl called the state police from a store several 
miles away 
kentucky state police detective robert foster said the girl who 
shot clopton initially had left louisville with him willingly 
but there obviously came time when she wanted to get away 
foster said 
the girls 18yearold sister however told the courierjournal 
of louisville that her sister was abducted 
she didnt run away her sister said everybody thought 
she ran away but she didnt 
another man 41yearold james r cable was arrested thursday 
night in louisville and charged with firstdegree rape and sodomy 
in connection with the case cable was being held in the larue 
county jail under 250000 bond on each count 
edlin said cable wasnt suspected in the killings but may have 
distributed the body parts his relationship with clopton who had 
been previously imprisoned for sodomy and rape was not immediately 
clear 
a journal found at the campsite chronicled at least three 
homicides in jefferson county located about 50 miles 
northeast of the search area said state police lt wayne edwards 
it contained some names of missing juveniles he said 
the louisville girl who was returned to her father told police 
she had been held against her will for three weeks chained to a 
tree and raped repeatedly 
the girl said she took a shotgun while the man slept in a tent 
and killed him with a single shot to the head 
a police report didnt indicate how she freed herself said 
larue county sheriff merle edlin 
apparently he didnt keep her chained at all times edlin 
said i think she stayed there under threats under fear for her 
life 
authorities unsuccessfully searched a threecounty area in 
central kentucky on friday for the bodies of the two other missing 
girls 
