<TEXT>
a strong earthquake shook a province 
near the costa rican border knocking out electricity in one town 
and snapping a gasoline pipeline 
however no major damage or injuries were reported fire 
department personnel told the associated press by telephone 
the quake which measured 61 on the richter scale struck 
chiriqui province 275 miles west of panama city friday night 
electricity was cut off for a few minutes in puerto armuelles 
along the costa rican border and a gasoline pipeline broke but was 
quickly repaired a fire department employee said 
physicist jaime toral of the university of panamas seismic 
institute said by telephone that the epicenter of the quake was 
near golfito costa rica along the panamanian border he said it 
struck at 824 pm and that an earlier tremor registered 43 on 
the richter scale 
the richter scale is a gauge of the energy released by an 
earthquake as measured by the ground motion recorded on a 
seismograph every increase of one number means the ground motion 
is 10 times greater 
an earthquake of 60 can cause severe damage 
</TEXT>
