problems by having the escort with the nurses 
val halamandarias president of the washingtonbased national 
association of home care said violence is rife in some drugridden 
neighborhoods and nurses are increasingly getting caught in the 
crossfire 
its a huge problem nationwide particularly in the big urban 
centers she said i cant think of a city over a million 
population that doesnt have a problem 
in providence security escorts have helped no nurses have 
reported being physically assaulted since the visiting nurse 
association began using unarmed security escorts almost a decade 
ago said vna spokeswoman cheryl lisi 
but as the violence has escalated so has the need for security 
and for money to pay for guards mrs mackenzie said 
insurance once paid for health care to patients while support 
from philanthropists and charitable organizations covered 
