a sharp earthquake jolted the 
eastern san francisco bay area rattling windows and sending 
merchandise tumbling from the shelves of stores 
the quake which measured 46 on the richter scale occurred at 
941 pm friday and was centered in walnut creek about 25 miles 
east of san francisco according to the us geological survey in 
menlo park 
the quake and two aftershocks one at 947 pm measuring 43 
and another at 959 measuring 25 occurred on the concord fault 
and were part of a swarm of mild quakes that shook the normally 
placid fault earlier this month said usgs spokeswoman lou page 
there were no reports of injuries or serious damage but the 
quake spilled items into store aisles in several communities 
susanne desser a waitress at the dennys restaurant in 
danville said that while some customers kind of get a kick out 
of earthquakes others lose their appetites 
a lot of people ordered the quake hit and they didnt want to 
eat she said 
in concord the sixstory mt diablo hospital really shook 
said nursing supervisor mary bacon 
there was a sudden crack and then a rolling that goes on and 
on she said some of the patients and some of the employees 
were shook up and were sick to their stomachs 
the quake knocked out power to 1300 customers in concord east 
of walnut creek and scattered outages were reported in nearby 
alamo said pacific gas amp electric spokesman brad thomas the bay 
area rapid transit district stopped service to check the tracks 
but trains resumed running at 1005 pm 
mild shaking also was felt at the press box at candlestick park 
where the san francisco giants were in the sixth inning of a game 
with the st louis cardinals 
tremors of up to 55 on the richter scale were felt in the bay 
area on april 6 and april 18 none caused any major damage 
the 71magnitude quake that hit the region oct 17 claimed 67 
lives and caused about 71 billion in damage 
the richter scale is a measure of ground motion as recorded on 
seismographs every increase of one number means a tenfold increase 
in magnitude 
an earthquake of 4 on the richter scale can cause moderate 
damage in the local area a 5 considerable damage a 7 reading is a 
major earthquake capable of widespread heavy damage 
