said he suffers from the results of cruel treatment 
castro has claimed there never has been an instance of torture 
in more than 31 years of the cuban revolution but here are some of 
musteliers complaints 
for two years he was held in a white cell with nothing but a 
500watt electric bulb the constant glare made him nearsighted 
and the condition is becoming progressively worse 
loud horns blown by guards to keep him from sleeping cost him 
40 percent of his hearing 
his arms and legs bear the scars of bayonet attacks by guards 
and his jaw was broken once musteliers legs still are inflamed 
from the last hunger strike 
he once was handcuffed to two other inmates and placed in a cell 
six feet high six long and three wide if two of them lay 
sidebyside the third had to lie on top because of the handcuffs 
after 24 hours mustelier managed to remove the handcuffs the 
guards threatened to put them back on but he said for you to 
put the chains back on youll have to kill us 
an officer sided with the inmates and although the three were 
kept in the cell several more days they were not handcuffed 
despite his prison ordeal mustelier looks surprisingly healthy 
perhaps younger than his 47 years seven weeks after ending his 
last hunger strike he has gained 40 pounds and worries about 
becoming fat 
if he is embittered he doesnt show it laughter often 
punctuates his stories of life in prison even his description of 
being overrun by roaches and mosquitos 
we used to say they were the big allies of our jailers he 
said 
did he ever count the days during his 105day hunger strike 
no because after counting them you worry and this weighs on 
you he said and laughed again 
yoga and an hour of physical exercise every day helped mustelier 
endure the long confinement like maria he found comfort in 
religion 
in his last hunger strike his rosary was always with him 
he showed a visitor a book of religious verses he had since 
1988 despite daily use it was nearly in mint condition 
he opened the book with great care not touching the pages 
beyond the margins 
every verse filled me with peace and tranquillity he said 
mustelier wrote love poems to maria whom he calls caruca and 
gave her a collection of them in september for their second wedding 
anniversary 
one translated from the spanish reads 
your appearance produces not only happiness but joy 
happiness is a momentary state of emotion joy is a state of 
satisfaction and deep feeling with that i will look upon you as a 
gift of spring 
