thousands of abortion opponents gathered in 
washington today trying to impress the nation with their strength 
at a rally for life on the grassy mall by the washington 
monument 
president bush was addressing the group by a remote telephone 
hookup vice president dan quayle was appearing in person along 
with catholic cardinals country and gospel singers and 
antiabortion leaders 
sponsors declined to predict the size of the crowd but hoped to 
