saying before this system is in place nato military presence on 
the territory of east germany should not be allowed 
de maiziere accompanied by his foreign defense and econimics 
ministers was greeted upon arrival in moscow by soviet premier 
nikolai i ryzhkov 
east germany has been a key component in the warsaw pact 
military alliance and an important trading partner with the 
soviets the soviets are seeking to preserve their current trade 
agreements with east germany which were made under the german 
nations former communist government 
the talks are a prelude to formal negotiations between the 
germanys and the four world war ii allies that divided them the 
soviet union united states britain and france 
foreign ministers from the six nations are to begin unification 
negotiations may 5 in bonn west germany 
de maiziere has said east germany would protect the security 
interests of the soviet union he has disagreed with west germanys 
insistence that a unified germany be a part of the north atlantic 
treaty organization 
de maiziere was quoted in a newspaper interview on saturday as 
saying that he and the soviets disagree with west germany on the 
alliance question 
but this is not a stumbling block there must be further 
negotiations about nato and the question of security i will make 
that clear in moscow de maiziere said according to the 
hamburgbased bild newspaper 
in dublin ireland soviet foreign minister eduard shevardnadze 
said in a newspaper interview saturday that a united germany should 
be militarily nonaligned and could belong to both nato and 
the warsaw pact 
