theatrical press agent before she married samuel spewack in 1922 
the couple became a successful playwriting and 
screenplaywriting team winning a tony award in 1949 for kiss me 
kate cole porter wrote the music for the show which became one 
of the most popular musical comedies of the modern stage 
mrs spewack and her husband also were praised for their 
collaboration on boy meets girl a 1935 lampoon of the 
hollywood mystique 
