the government calls the tax a community charge but the 
opposition socialist labor party and others have dubbed it the poll 
tax after a similar per capita tax that sparked a peasants revolt 
in 1381 
under the measure local services are paid for not by a property 
tax as in the past but by a per capita tax on everyone over 18 the 
rate is set by each local district and varies widely 
ridley said if the labor party took power they would keep the 
charge because they would have to face up to the reality of the 
need to restrain local government spending in the interests of 
overall economic management 
critics however say the new tax is unfair because unlike 
income tax it takes no account of an individuals ability to pay 
and poorer people must pay the same as wealthier people lowincome 
families and some other groups can get rebates of up to 80 percent 
under the new system 
violence broke out at antitax demonstrations around the country 
last month a demonstration by 40000 people in london on march 31 
turned into a sixhour riot with 86 civilians and 374 police 
injured and 339 people arrested 
mrs thatcher came to power in 1979 and is now in her third 
term the next general election is due by mid1992 
