former black panther johnny spain 
whose double murder conviction in a 1971 san quentin prison 
uprising was overturned because he was shackled during his trial 
will not be retried authorities said friday 
marin county district attorney jerry herman called the reversal 
of spains conviction a travesty and a gross miscarriage of 
justice but said in a statement that a retrial would serve no 
practical purpose 
since this case is now 19 years old and since the defendant 
spain has now been out of custody and led a crimefree life for 
three years it is impossible to believe that a conviction secured 
after a retrial would result in the defendant spain being 
resentenced to prison herman said 
spain 40 has been out of prison for just over two years he 
was freed in march 1988 after a judge ordered the state parole 
board not to consider the san quentin incident in deciding whether 
spain was suitable for parole from a 1967 murder conviction 
