other issues unresolved henderson again overturned the convictions 
in 1986 this time citing the 25 pounds of shackles jackson was 
forced to wear throughout the court proceedings from 1971 to 1976 
the chains sometimes attached for 10 to 12 hours a day 
hampered spains ability to communicate with his lawyer may have 
affected his decision not to testify and may have prejudiced the 
jury against him spain said 
